com.edugility.maven.liquibase

Class LiquibaseChangeLogArtifactsProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edugility.maven.liquibase.LiquibaseChangeLogArtifactsProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArtifactsProcessor

    public class LiquibaseChangeLogArtifactsProcessor
extends Object
implements ArtifactsProcessor
    An ArtifactsProcessor for use in conjunction with the artifact-maven-plugin that creates a Liquibase changelog aggregating changelog fragments found in a MavenProject's dependencies.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    The documentation for the artifact-maven-plugin

      • getChangeLogResourceNames

        public Collection<String> getChangeLogResourceNames()
        Returns the relative names of resources representing Liquibase changelog fragments that this LiquibaseChangeLogArtifactsProcessor will look for.

        This method may return null.

        Typically, this method returns a singleton Collection containing the text META-INF/liquibase/changelog.xml.

        Returns:
        a Collection of relative resource names representing Liquibase changelog fragments, or null
        See Also:
        setChangeLogResourceNames(Collection)

      • process

        public Collection<? extends Artifact> process(MavenProject project,
                                              Collection<? extends Artifact> artifacts,
                                              Log log)
                                       throws ArtifactsProcessingException
        Harvests jar: URLs from the supplied resolved Artifacts and lists them in topological order as <include> elements inside a generated Liquibase changelog file.

        This method never returns null.

        Specified by:
        process in interface ArtifactsProcessor
        Parameters:
        project - the MavenProject currently in effect; will not be null
        artifacts - a Collection of Artifacts representing the full, transitive set of resolved dependencies of the supplied MavenProject; will not be null
        log - a Log for logging to a Maven console; may be null
        Returns:
        the supplied artifacts
        Throws:
        ArtifactsProcessingException - if an error occurs
        See Also:
        ArtifactsProcessor
